{
  "info": {
    "name": "Loyalty Points App",
    "description": "JSON-RPC 2.0 API for the loyalty-points server. All methods are POSTed to the single /api endpoint. params MUST be a one-element array (the gorilla json2 codec unmarshals it into [1]interface{}). Public methods (Register, Login) need no token; Login's test script captures the returned token into the collection's {{token}} variable so protected calls inherit the Authorization header.\n\nImport into Requestly via Import -> Postman.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"UserRegistrationService.Register\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"email\": \"ada@example.com\",\n      \"password\": \"hunter2pw\",\n      \"name\": \"Ada Lovelace\",\n      \"accountName\": \"Primary Wallet\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "Public. Creates a user and opens their first wallet account atomically, returning an access token so the caller is logged in immediately."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('no JSON-RPC error', () => pm.expect(body.error, JSON.stringify(body.error)).to.be.undefined);",
                  "if (body.result && body.result.token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.result.token);",
                  "  console.log('token captured into {{token}}');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"EmailPasswordAuthenticator.Login\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"email\": \"ada@example.com\",\n      \"password\": \"hunter2pw\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "Public. Authenticates with email and password and returns an access token. The test script stores result.token into the {{token}} collection variable."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('no JSON-RPC error', () => pm.expect(body.error, JSON.stringify(body.error)).to.be.undefined);",
                  "pm.test('token returned', () => pm.expect(body.result.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.result.token);",
                  "console.log('token captured into {{token}}');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Protected",
      "description": "These require a valid token and a role permitted to call the method (RBAC enforced by the authorization middleware). Run Login first to populate {{token}}.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Wallet.ProcessTransaction (placeholder)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"Wallet.ProcessTransaction\",\n  \"params\": [\n    {\n      \"ref\": \"tx-1\",\n      \"account_id\": \"acc-1\",\n      \"kind\": \"earn\",\n      \"points\": 100,\n      \"occurred_at\": \"2026-06-01T10:00:00Z\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"id\": 1\n}"
            },
            "description": "PLACEHOLDER. The wallet JSON-RPC adaptor does not exist yet; method name and param field names mirror the CLI's provisional batch shape (cmd/cli/pkg/ingest/request.go) and must be aligned when the adaptor lands. Sends Authorization: Bearer {{token}}."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
